translations.5061607014595476183: Here you can manage fleio currencies. All currencies are relative to the default one, thus the cost of one unit of default currency is given in units of regular currency ( indirect quotation ). So, when you update exchange rates the regular currencies will show prices that are equivalent to one unit of default currency.

translations.5063954603124244550: New project name and description templates
translations.6124640150217893589: Fleio automatically creates OpenStack Projects for clients and gives them names and descriptions. You can customize the default name and description using a template with access to {$START_TAG_STRONG}client{$CLOSE_TAG_STRONG} attributes. It's {$START_TAG_STRONG}IMPORTANT{$CLOSE_TAG_STRONG} to keep in mind that the project name needs to be unique/different from all the other projects already present in OpenStack. You can make sure of that by using the "client.id" template attribute or any attribute you know it will be unique. The {$START_TAG_STRONG}client{$CLOSE_TAG_STRONG} object has many attributes, some of them include: id, first_name, last_name, company, country, phone, email, date_created and {$START_TAG_STRONG}id{$CLOSE_TAG_STRONG} is always unique.

translations.7251674472499827572: The messaging broker URLs where to listen for notifications. Multiple URLs can be specified, one per line. Fleio updates it's internal state using notifications from OpenStack services. translations.3533458570233100535: The notifications topic where notifications are sent by services or the fleio-collector service. Multiple topics can be specie, separated by ',' (ex: "notifications, notifications_bis"). Usually there is one topic called 'notifications'. If the fleio-collector service is used, the default topic is 'fleio'.
translations.179725121444633271: The OpenStack services send notifications to different exchanges. The default exchanges used by Fleio are: 'nova', 'neutron', 'openstack', 'glance'. If the fleio-collector service is used, only one exchange is required named by default 'fleio'.
translations.7118004976986934191: The pool name is required if multiple consumers listen to the same topic. If ceilometer is installed, set this to a valid name, like 'fleio'. translations.3547514038328609337: Set the minimum step size that can be used when extending or shrinking a volume.
